{"id":237,"date":"2022-12-22T18:00:45","date_gmt":"2022-12-22T18:00:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/?page_id=237"},"modified":"2023-04-17T16:43:55","modified_gmt":"2023-04-17T16:43:55","slug":"planning-resources","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/research\/autism-ready-libraries\/toolkit\/resources-2\/planning-resources\/","title":{"rendered":"Planning Resources"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/research-projects\/autism-ready-libraries\/toolkit\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-692\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/04\/Toolkit-Icon-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"75\" \/><\/a>\u00a0 \u00a0 <a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/research-projects\/autism-ready-libraries\/toolkit\/training\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-693\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/04\/Toolkit-Icon-5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"75\" \/><\/a>\u00a0 \u00a0 <a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/research-projects\/autism-ready-libraries\/toolkit\/resources-2\/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-694\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/04\/Toolkit-Icon-6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"75\" \/><\/a><\/h1>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Environmental Audit Checklist<\/span><\/h1>\n<p>Mitigating or removing sensory and physical access barriers in your library spaces is an important part of autism-inclusive services. The environmental audit is designed to help library professionals improve access to the library for autistic children and their families. This resource includes:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>A general area checklist &#8211; this checklist is best for common areas in your library<\/li>\n<li>A library program checklist &#8211; this checklist is best for meeting rooms and other program spaces in your library<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>This resource can help spark conversations among staff and management on how best to address accessibility concerns for autistic children and their families.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/02\/Environmental-Audit-Checklist_Autism-Ready-Libraries-.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-389 \" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Untitled-design-53.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" \/><\/a><strong><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\"><a style=\"color: #4b2e83;\" href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/02\/Environmental-Audit-Checklist_Autism-Ready-Libraries-.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Download Environmental Audit Checklist PDF<\/a><\/span><\/strong><\/p>\n<h1><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Autism-Inclusive Program Plans<\/span><\/h1>\n<p>It can be difficult to find informed guidance for autism-inclusive early literacy programs. Based on our research and co-designed with parents and caregivers of autistic children, we\u2019ve developed autism-inclusive early literacy programs plans and templates to help. The program plans and templates in these resources are designed to be inclusive of autistic children with a variety of sensory needs and learning differences. These resources include:<\/p>\n<p>Our Autism-Inclusive Early Literacy Program Plans resource includes:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>1 Basic Storytime Program Plan<\/li>\n<li>1 Virtual Storytime Program Plan<\/li>\n<li>1 Musical Storytime Program Plan for Sensory Seekers<\/li>\n<li>1 \u201cAll Activity\u201d Program Plan<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #4b2e83;\" href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Autism-Inclusive-Early-Literacy-Program-Plans_Autism-Ready-Libraries.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-389\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Untitled-design-53-e1678127456682.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" \/>\u00a0Download Autism-Inclusive Early Literacy Program Plans PDF<\/a><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p>Our Autism-Inclusive Storytime Templates resource includes:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>1 Basic Inclusive Storytime Template<\/li>\n<li>1 Virtual Inclusive Storytime Template<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\"><a style=\"color: #4b2e83;\" href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Autism-Inclusive-Early-Literacy-Storytime-Templates_Autism-Ready-Libraries.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-389\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Untitled-design-53-e1678127456682.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" \/>\u00a0Download Autism-Inclusive Early Literacy Storytime Templates PDF<\/a><\/span><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Below you will find examples to help you develop visual supports for autism-inclusive early literacy programs. These include an example visual schedule, and example slides for a virtual storytime:<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #4b2e83;\" href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Example-Visual-Schedule-Handouts-for-Storytime_Autism-Ready-Libraries.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-389\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Untitled-design-53-e1678127456682.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" \/>\u00a0Download Example Visual Schedule &amp; Handouts for Storytime PDF<\/a><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #4b2e83;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #4b2e83;\" href=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Virtual-Program-Example-Slides_-Autism-Ready-Libraries.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-389\" src=\"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/files\/2023\/03\/Untitled-design-53-e1678127456682.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"75\" height=\"75\" \/>\u00a0Download Virtual Program Example Slides PDF<\/a><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\"><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 Environmental Audit Checklist Mitigating or removing sensory and physical access barriers in your library spaces is an important part of autism-inclusive services. The environmental audit is designed to help library professionals improve access to the library for autistic children and their families. This resource includes: A general area checklist &#8211; this checklist is best for common areas in your library A library program checklist &#8211; this checklist is best for meeting rooms and other program spaces&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":20058,"featured_media":634,"parent":235,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-237","page","type-page","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/237","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sites.uw.edu\/neurodiversity\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/20058"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,